{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"1\n      \n        Hover-triggered navigation dropdowns\n        Current: onMouseEnter/onMouseLeave on Produccion/Gestion menus. Disappears when cursor drifts off. Unusable on touch devices.\n        Professional standard: Click-to-open with click-outside-to-close. Linear, Vercel, Stripe all use click-triggered menus. Hover menus are an anti-pattern for navigation.","choice":"nav-hover","id":null,"timestamp":1774837284255}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"2\n      \n        Emoji as UI iconography\n        Current: 40+ emojis used as icons: 🐄 🌾 💉 🏥 📦 💰 📊 📋 🐣 💀 🤒 etc. Renders differently across OS/browser. Looks unserious.\n        Professional standard: Consistent icon set (Lucide, Heroicons, or Phosphor). Monochrome, weight-matched, renders identically everywhere. Emoji reserved for user-facing content (chat), never for UI chrome.","choice":"emoji-abuse","id":null,"timestamp":1774837284610}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"3\n      \n        Inline collapsible forms push content around\n        Current: Every \"Add\" action inserts a form inline that shifts the entire page layout. User loses position. 8+ different form patterns, all inline.\n        Professional standard: Slide-over panels (drawers) or modals for data entry. Page stays stable. Linear uses right-side panels; Stripe uses modals. Content underneath doesn't move.","choice":"inline-forms","id":null,"timestamp":1774837284990}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"4\n      \n        Destructive actions with no confirmation\n        Current: \"Eliminar\" buttons directly call deleteSection(), deleteCattle(), etc. No confirmation dialog. One mis-tap deletes data permanently.\n        Professional standard: Confirmation dialog for all destructive actions. \"Are you sure? This will delete X and cannot be undone.\" Red-themed confirm button.","choice":"no-confirm-delete","id":null,"timestamp":1774837285415}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"5\n      \n        Loading states are emoji + animate-pulse text\n        Current: Loading shows a giant emoji (🌿, 📊, 💬) with pulsing \"Cargando...\" text. Feels amateur.\n        Professional standard: Skeleton screens that mirror the actual layout. Or a minimal spinner with no emoji. Vercel uses skeleton placeholders; Linear uses a subtle progress bar.","choice":"loading-emoji","id":null,"timestamp":1774837286152}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"6\n      \n        Select component is redefined in every page\n        Current: Identical Select component copy-pasted in hacienda, sanidad, agricultura, inventario, finanzas. Each one is the same 15 lines. Browser-native <select> styling is inconsistent across platforms.\n        Professional standard: One custom Select component with search/filter (like Radix or cmdk). Professional apps never use native <select> for more than 5 options.","choice":"select-component","id":null,"timestamp":1774837287164}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"7\n      \n        StatCard is visually flat and information-sparse\n        Current: Centered text with colored border. No trend indicator, no comparison, no sparkline. Just a big number and a label.\n        Professional standard: Left-aligned. Small icon. Value + delta/trend badge (\"12% vs last month\"). Optional sparkline. Stripe Dashboard is the gold standard here.","choice":"stat-cards","id":null,"timestamp":1774837287865}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"8\n      \n        No page headers or breadcrumbs\n        Current: Pages jump straight into content. No title, no description, no breadcrumb. User navigates to /produccion/sanidad and sees \"Vacunaciones\" section directly.\n        Professional standard: Every page has a header with title, optional description, and primary action button. Breadcrumbs for nested pages. Vercel pattern: \"Deployments\" + filter bar + \"Deploy\" button.","choice":"page-headers","id":null,"timestamp":1774837288961}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"9\n      \n        Tables lack professional data table features\n        Current: Raw HTML tables with no sorting, no pagination, no column resizing, no row selection. Action buttons are tiny \"Editar\"/\"Eliminar\" text links.\n        Professional standard: Sortable columns, pagination for 20+ rows, bulk actions via row selection, hover-revealed action menus (or right-click context menu). Think Linear's issue list.","choice":"table-design","id":null,"timestamp":1774837289282}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"10\n      \n        Color system is inconsistent and overloaded\n        Current: Emerald for primary, success, active nav, AND section colors. Red for errors AND expenses. Amber for warnings AND financial results. Same color means different things in different contexts.\n        Professional standard: Strict semantic color mapping. One primary action color. Separate semantic palette (success/warning/error). Data visualization uses a different palette entirely.","choice":"color-system","id":null,"timestamp":1774837290344}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"11\n      \n        Mobile bottom nav is too simple for 11+ pages\n        Current: 5 emoji-labeled buttons. \"Produccion\" goes to hacienda directly, no way to reach sanidad or agricultura from mobile nav. \"Gestion\" goes to inventario only.\n        Professional standard: Bottom nav with the 5 icons is fine, but tapping \"Produccion\" should show a sub-nav sheet or the SubTabBar should be visible on mobile pages. Users need to reach all sub-pages.","choice":"mobile-nav","id":null,"timestamp":1774837290660}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"12\n      \n        Typography hierarchy is too flat\n        Current: Nearly everything is text-sm (14px). Headers are text-xl (20px). Section headers are text-xs uppercase. Three sizes total across the entire app.\n        Professional standard: 5-6 size stops with clear hierarchy. Page title (24-28px), section title (18-20px), card title (16px), body (14px), caption (12px). Font weight variation: regular, medium, semibold.","choice":"typography","id":null,"timestamp":1774837292269}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"13\n      \n        No transitions or micro-animations\n        Current: Forms appear/disappear instantly (conditional rendering). No enter/exit animations. Dropdowns pop in with no transition. Page navigation has no loading indicator.\n        Professional standard: Subtle fade/slide for panels. Skeleton-to-content transitions. Dropdown menus with 150ms ease-out. Route change indicator (top progress bar like NProgress).","choice":"transitions","id":null,"timestamp":1774837292623}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"14\n      \n        Empty states are text-only with emoji\n        Current: Big emoji + one line of text. No illustration, no action button, no help link.\n        Professional standard: Illustrated empty state with a clear CTA button. \"No cattle registered yet\" + illustration + \"Add your first cattle\" button. Linear's empty states are a good reference.","choice":"empty-states","id":null,"timestamp":1774837293002}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"15\n      \n        Spacing is too tight throughout\n        Current: gap-2, gap-3 everywhere. Cards have p-3 or p-4. Everything feels dense and cramped. Tags are tiny (px-2 py-0.5).\n        Professional standard: More generous padding. Cards with p-5 or p-6. gap-4 between sections. Breathing room signals quality. Luxury = space.","choice":"spacing","id":null,"timestamp":1774837293411}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"16\n      \n        Login page feels like a hackathon project\n        Current: Giant 🐄 emoji as logo. \"CampoAI\" in emerald. Simple form box. No branding, no value prop, no visual identity.\n        Professional standard: Split layout (form left, hero/illustration right). SVG logo mark. Tagline with value proposition. Subtle background pattern or gradient. Trust signals.","choice":"login-page","id":null,"timestamp":1774837293777}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"17\n      \n        No success/error feedback after actions\n        Current: After saving a section, cattle, transaction — the form just closes. No toast, no notification, no visual confirmation that it worked. Only failure uses alert().\n        Professional standard: Toast notifications for all CRUD operations. \"Section created successfully\" with undo option. Error toasts with retry. Sonner or react-hot-toast.","choice":"toast-feedback","id":null,"timestamp":1774837294215}
